{"questionId":"9077010","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{15}^{32}{\\text{P}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>15</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>32</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is formed when a nucleus of deuterium (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{1}^{2}{\\text{H}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>H</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>) collides with a nucleus of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{15}^{31}{\\text{P}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>15</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>31</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>. The radius of a deuterium nucleus is 1.5 fm.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine, in J, the minimum initial kinetic energy that the deuterium nucleus&nbsp;must have in order to produce <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{15}^{32}{\\text{P}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>15</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>32</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.&nbsp;Assume that the phosphorus nucleus is&nbsp;stationary throughout the interaction and that only electrostatic forces act.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>energy required&nbsp;= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{15{e^2}}}{{4\\pi {\\varepsilon _0} \\times 5.3 \\times {{10}^{ - 15}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>15</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>ε</mi>\n          <mn>0</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>5.3</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>15</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>= 6.5 / 6.6 ×10<sup>−13</sup> <em><strong>OR</strong></em> 6.3 ×10<sup>−13 </sup>«J» ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Allow ecf from (b)(i)</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9077010","referenceCode":"18N.2.HL.TZ0.b.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine, in J, the minimum initial kinetic energy that the deuterium nucleus must have in order to produce 15 32 P . Assume that the phosphorus nucleus is stationary throughout t","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields","10.2 – Fields at work","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}